CALL FOR PAPERS


For further information:

www.specom2005.org


SECOND ANNOUNCEMENT AND CALL FOR PAPERS
SPECOM 2005

10th International Conference on Speech and Computer
October 17-19 2005
University of Patras, Patras, Greece

Organized by WCL, Department of Electrical & Computer Engineering, =
University of Patras, Greece
in collaboration with Moscow State Linguistic University (MSLU), Moscow, =
Russia

Supported by ISCA (International Speech Communication Association) and
ELSNET (European Network in Language and Speech)

AIMS
SPECOM 2005, the 10th International Conference on Speech and Computer, =
is following the events held up-to-now alternately in St. Petersburg and =
Moscow (Russia). The aim of this conference is to present and discuss =
new developments connected with natural human - computer interaction. In =
particular emphasis will be on the progress and challenges of speech and =
language technology applications.

=20

The scientific program will include several invited lectures as well as =
submitted paper presentations. Submitted papers will be published in a =
volume of proceedings available at the conference.



TOPICS

Topics of interest for paper submission include but are not limited to:

=A7         Speech production and perception

=A7         Speech analysis and processing

=A7         Natural language processing

=A7         Speech coding and transmission

=A7         Speech recognition and understanding

=A7         Speech synthesis

=A7         Spoken dialog systems

=A7         Speaker recognition

=A7         Multi-modal processing

=A7         Speech and language resources

=A7         Applied systems for Human-Computer Interaction=20

=20

VENUE

The conference will be held at the Conference Centre of the University =
of Patras, Greece. Patras is located on the west coast of Greece, 200 km =
from Athens. It is the principal seaport linking the country with Italy =
and the commercial and cultural centre of Western Greece. Apart from its =
beautiful landscape, Patras is close to the famous archeological sites =
of Olympia, Delphi and Corinth.

=20

SUBMISSION OF PAPERS

Prospective authors are invited to submit full papers of not more than =
four (4) pages. Paper submission will be done exclusively via the =
conference website, using the submission guidelines. All papers will be =
refereed by an International Scientific Committee. Submission of a paper =
implies a commitment to present the paper if accepted.

=20

IMPORTANT DATES

Submission of full paper: <deadline>June 27, 2005</deadline>

Notification of acceptance: July 18, 2005

Early registration: July 29, 2005

Late registration: September 10, 2005

Conference:    October 17-19, 2005

=20

LANGUAGE

The official language of the conference will be English.

=20

